"Stooges?" TARANUTULUS said with obviously feigned innocence, "I have
only the soldiers that Hydras, in his infinite wisdom, chose to leave
behind." He gestured at SCAREM and IGUANUS.

Gesturing languidly TARANTULUS continued, "With no command staff to
speak of, who was left to take over and make sure that his base was
just as he left it?"

"And I completed the task that Hydras left behind." TARANTULUS
Directed his hand at the dark armored female as he smiled, "Meet
Antagony."

"Fine." SKYSHADOW grunted, "Then what is to stop us from retaking Hydras' seat?"

TARANTULUS smiled wickedly, "Because the female has information for us
that I think you will want to hear."

With her every movement graceful and controlled, almost like a dancer
ANTAGONY turned to face the others.  "There is a rip in your time
space continuum." She said coolly and matter-of-factually. "On that
will only get bigger."

There was a wicked chuckle, "Besides me . . . and Antagony here, who
knows how to fix one of them, hmmm?"

More cackling from TARANTULUS.

(TAG)

- Preston
